%N A183674 Number of (n+1) X 2 0..7 arrays with every 2 X 2 subblock summing to 14.
%H A183674 R. H. Hardin, <a href="/A183674/b183674.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..189</a>
%H A183674 Christian Krause, <a href="/A183674/a183674.txt">Proof of formulas</a>, Jun 12 2026
%F A183674 a(n) = 36*a(n-1) - 546*a(n-2) + 4536*a(n-3) - 22449*a(n-4) + 67284*a(n-5) - 118124*a(n-6) + 109584*a(n-7) - 40320*a(n-8).
%F A183674 G.f.: 8*x*(43 - 1288*x + 15799*x^2 - 102256*x^3 + 374218*x^4 - 766288*x^5 + 801072*x^6 - 322560*x^7) / ((1 - x)*(1 - 2*x)*(1 - 3*x)*(1 - 4*x)*(1 - 5*x)*(1 - 6*x)*(1 - 7*x)*(1 - 8*x)). - _Colin Barker_, Apr 02 2018
%F A183674 a(n) = 8*8^n + 14*7^n + 12*6^n + 10*5^n + 8*4^n + 6*3^n + 4*2^n + 2. - _Christian Krause_, Jun 12 2026
%F A183674 E.g.f.: 2*(4*exp(8*x) + 7*exp(7*x) + 6*exp(6*x) + 5*exp(5*x) + 4*exp(4*x) + 3*exp(3*x) + 2*exp(2*x) + exp(x) - 32). - _Stefano Spezia_, Jun 18 2026
%e A183674 Some solutions for 3 X 2:
%e A183674 ..5..0....1..5....3..3....0..5....2..7....2..4....2..2....5..6....2..4....0..6
